> This is expected and not related to quadlet. networks that have dns_enabled set to true (i.e. all new bridge networks by default unless --disable-dns is used) will use aarvavark-dns and therefore will have the aardvark-dns ip in resolv.conf. That does not mean --dns is ignored, the dns is server is simply passed to aaravark-dns instead and it will forward to these server for the specific container requests.

Thank you, now my DNS problem in my container works. Cost me many hours. But I still don't understand why aardvark-dns doesn't work when it's enabled. Oh well, at least now I have a workaround. 

@fansari Thanks for your issue
